  "course_description": "A seminar for advanced students on topics of current interest in chemistry.",
  "course_notes": "The course reviews how metals function in biological systems, highlighting unique properties of these elements that enable essential processes in living organisms. Topics covered include structure and reactivity of metal sites in biomolecules, cellular utilization of naturally occurring metals, and use of exogenous metals in medicine.",
